Package CommonLib.messages

'message' package contains all the messages mechanism of the communication between the client and the server.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IMessageData
    MessageData: Describes the actual data which contained in the message, implementing types must contain unique 'serialVersionUID'.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EntitiesListData
    ManyEntityData: Describes a IMessageData that contains a List of IEntity and an operation to execute on all of them.
    EntityData
    AddEntityData: Describes a IMessageData that contains an IEntity and an operation to execute on it.
    EntityDataCollection
    EntityDataCollection: Describes a IMessageData that contains a List of EntityData.
    LoginData
    LoginData: Describes the required data to login message, the type used by Message.
    Message
    Message: Define messages that are described by ID, creation time and Object data.
    MessagesFactory
    MessagesFactory: Factory of Message.
    RespondMessageData
    AddEntityData: Is a class that contains a respond to request, the class contains the requested IMessageData and a boolean respond if request execution succeed or failed.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    EntityDataOperation
    EntityDataOperation: An operation which does on EntityData.

Package CommonLib.messages Description

'message' package contains all the messages mechanism of the communication between the client and the server.

'Common' project contains interfaces and classes which are shared both to the server and to the client.
